SIMPLE: heighten
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heighten
<hw>Height"en</hw> <pr>(h⟦imac⟧t"'n)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>highten</asp>.]</altsp> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Heightened</conjf> <pr>(#)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Heightening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make
high; to raise higher; to elevate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To carry forward; to advance; to increase; to
augment; to aggravate; to intensify; to render more conspicuous; -- used
of things, good or bad; <as>as, to <ex>heighten</ex> beauty; to
<ex>heighten</ex> a flavor or a tint.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧To
<xex>heighten</xex> our confusion.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An aspect of mystery which was easily <qex>heightened</qex> to the
miraculous.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heightener</ent>⟦br⟧
